description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Band 2 Clinic/ Telephone Clerk&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Exciting new post has arisen within the Maternity Administration Team at St Mary’s Hospital.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Full-time, Substantive contract - &lt;/strong&gt;9am to 5pm Monday to Friday (excluding Bank Holidays).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful applicant will provide a high quality day-to-day Admin service to our teams, and will be highly motivated and organised individual. You will be required to work autonomously and be able to prioritise your own workload.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will provide effective and efficient clerical, reception and administrative support to the Maternity Outpatient and community Clinics, ensuring the administration processes meet the needs of all service users. You will be working as part of a multidisciplinary team alongside our busy midwives. This may require the post-holders to work at Queen Charlotte’s &amp; Chelsea Hospital in the event of absence.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you have the ability to multi-task in an administrative role, with a flexible “can-do” attitude to work and can see yourself as part of a busy multidisciplinary team then we would like to hear from you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Due to the popularity of some positions, we reserve the right to close the vacancy early on receipt of sufficient applicants.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Festus Ajala - Administration Manager on 020 33122327&lt;/p&gt;
